Newkirk Public Schools 9.4.2020
Effective immediately all students will eat free of charge. The USDA announced they are extending free meals to kids till the end of the year or till funds run out. We still need you to fill out a meal application if you have not done so. Whichever takes place first Dec.31, 2020 or funds run out we will go back to charging for meals based on your application.

shared_text:
Newkirk Public Schools
September 2 at 5:21 PM ·

Newkirk Public Schools had a COVID-19 TRACE today that affected a very small number of students isolated to the HS. A contract trace is when an individual that test positive is in colse proximity for an extended time to another individual. This was only a trace, so NO Newkirk student or staff member tested positive for COVID-19 today. We worked with the Kay County Health Department and an investigation has taken place. Parents, please continue to follow the attendance questionnaire before sending your child to school. Newkirk will continue to proceed in our current in-class (green) schedule.

shared_text:
Newkirk Public Schools
August 22 at 2:45 PM ·

Newkirk Public Schools had a positive COVID-19 case this morning with one of our support staff employees. We worked with the Kay County Health Department and an investigation has taken place. No students or staff members (aside from primary family members) have been exposed. Masks and social distancing were key in limiting exposure in this incident. On a daily basis, staff members are wearing masks when social distancing is not possible. We are strongly encouraging students to wear masks to help limit exposure for future possible incidents. Newkirk will continue to proceed in our current in-class (green) schedule.

post_text: Class Schedule pick up day is on Tuesday, August 4th from 9:00 to 12:00 and 1:00 to 3:00. Students will need to have completed the online enrollment in order for their schedule to be released. If you need your snapcode, call the office and we will get it for you. We will also be collecting Class Dues which is $30, Technology Fee which is $25 for the first student and $10 for each additional sibling in the family, this is for a student issued Chromebook, lunch acct money, and if you need a parking permit they will be available for $10.00. If you are wanting to have your student on the Virtual Online Plan please call the high school, so we can sign them up. Hope to see you Tuesday, we are looking forward to a great year.

shared_text:
Newkirk Public Schools
June 30 at 3:38 PM ·

Dear Newkirk,
My name is Scott Kempenich and I am excited to serve Newkirk Public School as the new Superintendent. I grew up in Wagoner and attended the University of Oklahoma where I was blessed enough to be a part of the 2000 National Championship. I have been married for twenty-two years to Christa and we have two children, Jaxon and Gracie. I have served as an educator for a total of nineteen years, the last twelve years I have served as a school administrator. I have been a teacher, coach, assistant principal, principal and superintendent in my professional career. I am an educational leader that strives to provide the best education possible to all students. I know there are many questions about what the school year will look like in this new era of Covid-19. In the next several weeks we will be working diligently to create safe schooling options for all employees and students in the 2020-2021 school year. I look forward to meeting all school employees, students, parents and community members.
text:
Newkirk Public Schools
June 30 at 3:38 PM ·

Dear Newkirk,
My name is Scott Kempenich and I am excited to serve Newkirk Public School as the new Superintendent. I grew up in Wagoner and attended the University of Oklahoma where I was blessed enough to be a part of the 2000 National Championship. I have been married for twenty-two years to Christa and we have two children, Jaxon and Gracie. I have served as an educator for a total of nineteen years, the last twelve years I have served as a school administrator. I have been a teacher, coach, assistant principal, principal and superintendent in my professional career. I am an educational leader that strives to provide the best education possible to all students. I know there are many questions about what the school year will look like in this new era of Covid-19. In the next several weeks we will be working diligently to create safe schooling options for all employees and students in the 2020-2021 school year. I look forward to meeting all school employees, students, parents and community members.

Grades 8th thru 11th if you would like to apply for a class office for the school year 2020-2021, send Mrs. Mayse a resume at dmayse@newkirk.k12.ok.us Make sure you include the office you are running for. Mrs Mayse will notify you if you have an opponent running for the same office. Application needs to be in by April 17th, 2020. You are welcome to campaign through social media. Voting will take place on May 4th, 2020. Everyone check your email to place your vote on this day. Good Luck!

post_text: Students interested in concurrent enrollment for 2020-21: You will need to call the college you plan on attending and check on how they are handling enrollment in regards to COVID-19. To qualify for concurrent enrollment, you will need a COMPOSITE SCORE of 19 on the Pre-ACT or ACT or a 3.0 GPA. In order to enroll, you will need an official high school transcript and a concurrent permission form. Both of these are obtained through the high school office. You will need to call the high school to find out how you can get these documents. Once you have enrolled, you will need to email Ms. Rowe a copy of your schedule. If you have any questions, please email Ms. Rowe at prowe@newkirk.k12.ok.us

April 1st, 2020
Update on Meal pick- ups and delivery times:
Starting April 6th we will provide meals Monday, Wednesday and Thursday 9:00am-11:00am.
We are still providing enough meals for the entire week. Monday you will receive meals for Monday and Tuesday, Wednesday meals for Wednesday, Thursday you will receive meals for Thursday and Friday.
This new schedule will allow us to provide some hot meals along with reducing person to person contact, keeping student and employee’s safe in this unprecedented time.
Please read the Food Safety, Storage and Reheat instructions on storing food.

post_text:
Concurrent Enrollment at OU provides eligible high school juniors and seniors the opportunity to enroll in college courses at the University of Oklahoma while they are still in high school.

Sooner Discovery
This summer, students can amplify their Concurrent Enrollment experience by living on campus for four weeks during the summer, take five hours of college credit, and experience life as a Sooner with our Sooner Discovery program. Sooner Discovery’s goal is to provide high school students a unique and full college immersion experience. Visit ou.edu/soonerdiscovery to learn more.

Concurrent Enrollment
Students can also take classes online or on campus this summer by applying for Concurrent Enrollment. Rising Oklahoma seniors will receive a tuition waiver from the state for up to 18 hours their senior year, so all they would have to pay is a reduced fee rate of $80 per hour! Visit ou.edu/concurrent to learn more.

post_text: Newkirk Public Schools has adopted a new Student Information System software this year. That new software is PowerSchool. You will have access to your child’s grades and attendance via the PowerSchool website and app on your smartphone. For grades 6-12, you will be receiving your ID’s and Passwords in the mail tomorrow or Monday. For grades PK-5, that information will be in your child’s Tuesday folder next week. Since we are changing Student Information Systems, there will be a few issues along the way. We are working those out at this time, but for the most part, the problems have been solved.

Newkirk Public Schools
May 8, 2019 at 1:49 PM ·

Newkirk Public Schools will be in session tomorrow. May 9th, 2019.

Due to Tuesday night/Wednesday morning storms, Newkirk High School will be offering community service tomorrow throughout the day. (The middle school and elementary will be in session, but may do some community service throughout the day as well). The main goal with this is to do tree limb removal throughout the town from whomever may need it.

We will be asking high schools students, as well as faculty to bring some of the following items.
1. Gloves
2. Work clothes
3. rakes
4. closed toe shoes or boots
5. Trailers - If you bring a trailer, park your vehicle at the gym in the morning. A teacher will meet you there.
6. If you do not have a trailer, meet in the commons as normal.
